main event: Multiple bright, glowing, and pulsating lights were observed in the night sky over Phoenix, Arizona, on March 3, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be stationary at an estimated altitude of 2000 to 3000 feet.
After an unspecified period of time, the objects began to move in a southerly direction while maintaining their stationary posture.
No sound was reported by the witnesses.
Photographic evidence in the form of 8mm movie film was obtained during the incident by a local resident, and the film was being processed and analyzed by the United States Air Force.
The investigator was unable to determine the origin or nature of the unidentified objects, and the case was being forwarded to Project Blue Book for further evaluation and study.
sighted object: numerous bright, glowing, and pulsating lights in the night sky
witnesses: multiple witnesses in the Phoenix metropolitan area
photographs: yes, 8mm movie film was obtained by a local resident
